  <p class="osos-note">Source: councillors' own biography pages (<a href="https://www.sagamokanishnawbek.com/sagamok-team-members/arnelda-bennett" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Arnelda Bennett</a>, <a href="https://www.sagamokanishnawbek.com/sagamok-team-members/sadie-southwind" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sadie Southwind</a>). This counts only what these two Councillors chose to list; the full committee roster is not published, so the real number of committee seats held across Council is higher.</p>

  {% include 'components/section_heading.html.twig' with { title: 'The principle' } only %}
  <blockquote class="osos-quote">
    "Chief and Council&hellip; oversee the work of the organization."
    <cite>Sagamok Anishnawbek, <a href="https://www.sagamokanishnawbek.com/chief-council" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chief and Council page</a></cite>
  </blockquote>
  <p>A councillor helps set the budgets, approves the spending, and oversees the managers of the administration. When that same councillor is also an employee of the administration, they are on both sides of the table: overseeing the very body that employs and pays them. This is not a question about any one person's work. It is a question about the structure.</p>
  <p>The more tables a person sits at, the bigger the cheque. The Councillor who holds only her seat was paid $22,850 in the year ending March 2025; the one who is also a company president was paid $200,365, more than the Chief. Pay figures come from the FNFTA Schedule of Remuneration and Expenses, which folds all pay from the Nation and its companies into one number per Councillor.</p>

  {% include 'components/section_heading.html.twig' with { title: 'The ask' } only %}
  <div class="osos-ask">
    <p><strong>Choose a role.</strong> A member gets none of these; thirteen leaders hold fifty-five. How many is one person allowed to hold? One paid public role each: keep the seat, or keep the job, not a fistful of both. No elected leader also drawing a staff salary, and the paid board and committee seats shared across the community, not stacked on the same few people.</p>
  </div>

  {% include 'components/section_heading.html.twig' with { title: 'Right of reply' } only %}
  <p>Chief and Council have been asked directly to confirm this information is current and to submit any corrections. Any correction they provide will be reflected here.</p>

